  "author_association": "NONE",
  "body": "* Feature Request\r\n\r\n**What should the feature do:**\r\nWhen using a StorageClassDeviceSet to configure OSDs, allow multiple volumeClaimTemplates with different storageClassNames to be defined as described in the following example: https://github.com/rook/rook/blob/master/design/ceph/storage-class-device-set.md#example-5-multiple-devices-per-osd. This is needed to achieve optimal performance by allowing metadata to be stored on an SSD PVC and data to be stored on a HDD PVC.\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\nRook 1.1 on OCP 3.11",
